# Now going to setup some of the first parts of the model in order to
img_shape = (28, 28, 1)
batch_size = 16
latent_dim = 2

# Setting up input and convolutional network
input_img = Input(shape=img_shape)

x = Conv2D(32, 3, padding='same', activation='relu')(input_img)
x = Conv2D(64, 3, padding='same', activation='relu', strides=(2, 2))(x)
x = Conv2D(64, 3, padding='same', activation='relu')(x)
x = Conv2D(64, 3, padding='same', activation='relu')(x)

shape_before_flattening = K.int_shape(x)

x = Flatten()(x)
x = Dense(32, activation='relu')(x)

z_mean = Dense(latent_dim)(x)
z_log_var = Dense(latent_dim)(x)

# Getting sampling method for the mean and log variance

def sampling(args):
    z_mean, z_log_var = args
    epsilon = K.random_normal(shape=(K.shape(z_mean)[0], latent_dim), mean=0., stddev=1.)
    return z_mean + K.exp(z_log_var) * epsilon

z = Lambda(sampling)([z_mean, z_log_var])

x = Reshape(shape_before_flattening[1:])(x)
x = Conv2DTranspose(32, 3, padding='same', activation='relu', strides=(2, 2))(x)
x = Conv2D(1, 3, padding='same',activation='sigmoid')(x)

# Setting up decoder for the model
decoder = Model(decoder_input, x)
z_decoded = decoder(z)

# Custom Variational Layer for learning
class CustomVariationalLayer(Layer):
    # Loss calculation for vae
    def vae_loss(self, x, z_decoded):
        x = K.flatten(x)
        z_decoded = K.flatten(z_decoded)
        xent_loss = metrics.binary_crossentropy(x, z_decoded)
        kl_loss = -5e-4 * K.mean( 1 + z_log_var - K.square(z_mean) - K.exp(z_log_var), axis=-1)
        return K.mean(xent_loss + kl_loss)

    # Function that executes when data is going throug this custom layer
    def call(self, inputs):
        x = inputs[0]
        z_decoded = inputs[1]
        loss = self.vae_loss(x, z_decoded)
        self.add_loss(loss, inputs=inputs)
        return x

# Creating and initializing instance 
y = CustomVariationalLayer()([input_img, z_decoded])

# This is going to be a 15x15 grid of number digit pictures 
n=15
digit_size = 28

# Setting up grid and getting sizes ready in order to render it
figure = np.zeros((digit_size * n, digit_size * n))
grid_x = norm.ppf(np.linspace(0.05, 0.95, n))
grid_y = norm.ppf(np.linspace(0.05, 0.95, n))

# Enumerating through each one of the grids
for i, yi in enumerate(grid_x):
    for j, xi in enumerate(grid_y):
        # Rendering data via the decoder's prediction and placing it singular figures
        z_sample = np.array([[xi, yi]])
        z_sample = np.tile(z_sample, batch_size).reshape(batch_size, 2)
        x_decoded = decoder.predict(z_sample, batch_size=batch_size)
        digit = x_decoded[0].reshape(digit_size, digit_size)
        figure[i * digit_size: (i + 1) * digit_size, j * digit_size: (j + 1) * digit_size] = digit

# Display the images
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
plt.imshow(figure, cmap='Greys_r')
plt.show()
